This review is a true story. In 2017 I had a Super Bowl Party at my house. 
I had just moved to Philadelphia and only knew a few people and figured 
this would be a good way to get new friends. I told everyone to bring 
anyone they wanted. This one friend was bringing his girlfriend. At the 
last second, the guy texted me and asked if her sister could come along 
too. I said sure, why not? No joke, this girl walks in and she's the most 
beautiful woman I've ever seen. I couldn't believe it. She sat in the 
corner and wasn't really talking with anybody. I gave her some space for a 
little bit but then decided to find a reason to talk to her. I quickly 
Googled "funniest game apps" and Stray Dog Simulator showed up on the list. 
Perfect. It only took about a minute and a half to download. I quickly 
spent a couple of minutes figuring out how to play the game, making sure I 
knew enough about it. Then I went and sat down next to her. I said "Hey, so 
I know you're not really watching the Super Bowl...wanna see this game I'm 
playing?" She thought the game was really funny and we both laughed about 
it as she watched me attack a couple of Golden Retrievers. We ended up 
hanging out and talking for a bit. Immediately I thought she was the 
funniest and cutest girl I had ever met. It turned out she had a boyfriend, 
but she broke up with him a few weeks later. We started dating immediately 
after and now, a year and a half later, we're talking about getting 
engaged. To this day she says she knew that she liked me as soon as I 
started talking to her about the game. I owe my future wife and kids to 
this game. I guess you could say we are in the same dog pack now. Five 
stars.

I spent two hours in a meeting this morning trying to get my dachshund to ride the rollercoaster and it was becoming increasingly difficult to hide my frustrations from my work colleagues.  Despite the fact both I and the dachshund wanted it to happen, I still could not get it to ride the rollercoaster and I now feel unsure of where I stand.  4/5 stars - final star awaits collection when the dachshund / rollercoaster bug has been addressed.
